46.notes: Robust osteoblast–osteocyte program: TFs (SATB2, RUNX2, MEF2C), matrix genes (COL1A1/22A1/24A1, IBSP, OMD, CHAD), osteogenic enzymes (ALPL, PHOSPHO1), maturation markers (BGLAP, DMP1, SOST, PHEX, SPP1), and mineralisation/remodelling factors (MMP13, DKK1). Represents committed bone-forming cells transitioning toward osteocytes.

47.notes: Canonical erythroid program: globins (HBA1/2, HBB, HBG1/2, HBQ1, HBM) with chaperone AHSP; TFs (KLF1, GATA1, TAL1, NFE2); heme biosynthesis (ALAS2, FECH, UROD, HMBS, CPOX); structural/membrane genes (ANK1, SPTA1, SPTB, EPB42, GYPA/B/C/E, RHAG, RHD, RHCE, KEL, XK); iron import (TFRC, SLC25A37/39); and cycling markers (MKI67, BIRC5, CDK1, CENPF, TOP2A, CDC20).

48.notes: Chondro-osteogenic progenitor program: TFs (SOX6, RUNX2, MEIS2, MEOX2, EYA1, LEF1), BMP pathway (BMP5, BMPR1B, BMPER), ECM (COL24A1/25A1/27A1, COL9A1/2, COL2A1, COL8A1, HAPLN1), periosteal regulators (THBS2, POSTN, ITGBL1, ADAMTS family), and axon-guidance signalling (ROBO1/2, UNC5C/D, CNTN1/4, SEMA3A/D/E, EPHA3/5/6); plus mesenchymal regulators (HMGA2, ABI3BP, FNDC1, FRAS1).

49.notes: Strong myogenic program: TFs (MYOG, PAX7, SOX6, RBM24, HES6, PROX1), sarcomeric components (ACTC1, ACTA1, ACTN2, MYL4, MYLPF, MYPN, TNNT1/2, TNNI1/2, TPM2, TTN, NEB, RYR1, SGCA, DES), fusion/differentiation genes (MYMX, KLHL41, TRIM55, MRLN, CFL2), energy handling (ENO3, SRL, COX7A1, mitochondrial genes), and stress response (CRYAB, HSPB2, HSPH1).

50.notes: ECM-rich tendon/ligament program: TNMD, POSTN, THBS4, ASPN, FMOD, KERA, collagens (COL1A1, COL3A1, COL24A1). Periosteal developmental signalling (MEOX2, MEIS2, EYA1, BMP family, SFRP4) and guidance/adhesion molecules (DCHS2, DOCK4, CSMD3, ROBO1, CNTN5, EPHA7, EPHA3, ITGA2/8, CDH12).

51.notes: Strong epithelial program with keratins (KRT5/8/15/17/18/19), desmosomes (DSC3, DSG3, DSP), adhesion/ECM (COL17A1, CLDN4, NPNT, ITGA2/6), epithelial TFs (GRHL2, TP63, ELF5, TFAP2B), and basal progenitor markers (MIR205HG, S100A14, ESRP1, CXCL14).

52.notes: B lineage with activation: BCR components and Igs (IGHM, IGKC, CD79B, VPREB3, PAX5, ELL2, MYB); activation/GC regulators (BACH2, IKZF1/2, CD69, CD83, CD38); antigen presentation (HLA-DRA, HLA-B, CD74); NF-κB signalling (NFKB1, TNFAIP3, CARD11, BIRC3); trafficking (CXCR4, ITGA4, TAGAP, LTB, CYTIP).

53.notes: Synovial/joint fibroblast ECM program (COL6A6, COL3A1, COL4A1, TNXB, POSTN, ADAMTS family, FNDC1, ABI3BP, SPARCL1) with developmental TFs (EBF2, TSHZ2, MEOX2, MEIS2, CREB5). Joint niche signalling (IL7, IGF1, NRG1, CALCRL, BMPR1B, DKK2, SULF1).

54.notes: Classic cartilage matrix program with collagens (COL2/9/11), proteoglycans (ACAN, EPYC, HAPLN1), and glycoproteins (COMP, MATN family). TFs (SOX9, SOX6, NFATC2) confirm chondrogenic identity; broad cartilage-forming chondrocytes covering growth plate and articular contexts.

56.notes: PRG4⁺/CREB5⁺ synovial identity with ECM remodeling/stromal fibroblast markers. Mild chondrocyte program (SOX9, COL27A1) suggests a synovial-cartilage interface population. Likely interzone-derived synovial fibroblasts.

55.notes: Strong G2/M program (UBE2C, BIRC5, CDK1, CCNB1, CDC20, TPX2, NUSAP1, PCLAF, RRM2) with histones/tubulins. Lineage tilt via KRT8/18, NNAT, HES5/6, TUBB3/UCHL1 indicating epithelial/neuroepithelial progenitors rather than mesenchymal or immune.

57.annotation: Developing sensory/autonomic neurons (PHOX2B+/ISL1+, synaptic program active)
57.notes: Pan-neuronal and presynaptic machinery (STMN2, GAP43, ELAVL family, RBFOX1, PCLO/RIMS/CADPS) with ion channels (SCN*, CACNA*). Autonomic/visceral sensory identity suggested by PHOX2B, ISL1 and neurosecretory granins (CHGA/B, SCG2/3, NXPH1).

58.notes: Neuronal adhesion/axon guidance (CTNNA2, DCC, CTNND2), upper-layer/callosal cue (CUX2), neurogenesis lncRNAs (RMST, LINC00461), neuronal splicing (SRRM4) and synaptic machinery (NRXN1/3, RIMS/ ERC2, CADPS, PTPRN2). Ion channels/receptors (SCN3A, CACNA1B, KCNH7/8, GRIA2/4) support developing cortical-like glutamatergic identity distinct from PHOX2B+/ISL1+ autonomic neurons.

59.notes: Classical neutrophil granule and antimicrobial program (S100A8/A9/A12, MPO, ELANE, PRTN3, DEFA3/4, CAMP, LTF, BPI), with CEACAM8/6, CD177 and oxidative burst machinery (CYBB/NCF1). Myeloid regulators MNDA/MYB/IKZF1 present.

60.notes: Prenatal tissue-resident/anti-inflammatory macrophage profile with MRC1, CD163, LYVE1, STAB1, CSF1R; remodeling and tolerance genes (HMOX1, RNASE1, HPGDS). Likely perivascular niche-associated.

61.annotation: Schwann cell precursors (immature glial, neural crest–derived)
61.notes: Immature Schwann/glial precursor program. S100B, MPZ, PLP1, CDH19, CDH6, NCAM2, GFRA3 indicate Schwann lineage. ADGRG6 (GPR126) critical for Schwann development. EDNRB, SOX2-OT, HMGA2 reflect neural crest precursor state. Not strongly neuronal (lacks STMN2/ELAVL4 dominance).
